@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}R e q u i r e m e n t s . .@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

    - Any Amiga working on OS 2.1 or bigger,
    - (fast) MIDI-Interface



   @{b}Make sure that your MIDI-Instrument..@{ub}

     a)  MIDI-In/-Out are connected to your Amiga

     b)  SysEx is enabled
        ( MIDI GLOBAL -> MIDI Filter -> EX:ENA )

     c)  Global MIDI-Channel is set to 1
        ( MIDI GLOBAL -> CH=1 )
@endnode

@node "HowToUse" "HowToUse"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}H o w   t o   u s e . .@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}


   When you start KorgMAN, the standard (preset) bank is loaded.

   Although most functions are selfexplaing, here's a short
   description of all functions:



 @{b}@{u}Gadgets:@{ub}@{uu}


   @{i}Insert@{ui}
            Move active program to another position.
            Programs between new/old position are shifted.


   @{i}Exchange@{ui}
            Active program with another one


   @{i}Copy@{ui}
            Active program over another one


   @{i}Type@{ui}
            Choose instrumental category


 @{b}@{u}Menu's:@{ub}@{uu}

 @{i} @{b}@{u}@{ui}Project..@{ub}@{uu}

  @{i} Load/Save program@{ui}
            Load program to current position/
            Save current program to disk


   @{i}Load/Save bank@{ui}
            Load/Save current bank from/to disk


   @{i}Save ASCII@{ui}
            Write bank as ASCII-File.
  @{fg highlight}N e w  !@{fg text}  Save-ASCII-Pref's allows you
            too choose some parameters.


 @{b}@{u}Functions..@{ub}@{uu}

   @{i}MultiType@{ui}
            Set Type for more than one program

   @{i}Sorting@{ui}
            Sort bank by name and/or type

   @{i}DoubleCheck@{ui}
            Check bank for programs load twice

    
 @{b}@{u}Options..@{ub}@{uu}

   @{i}DoubleCheck@{ui}
            Don't mix this up with the similar function !
            Enabling this option advises KorgMAN to check each
            program loaded if it's already there.


   @{i}TestSound@{ui}
              Choose between 4 different melodys..


   @{i}InsSelect@{ui}
              Select between 03R/W and 05R/W to set the
              correct ID-Byte for the SysEx-Header-String..
@endnode

@node "OldFiles" "Oldfiles"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}U s i n g   o l d   f i l e s  . .@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}


   KorgMAN will automatically decide if a sound/bank-file
   is an old (<1.5) or new one and convert it if necessary.

   If you've got any problems loading old files, please
   contact me  (including the sound/bank-file !)
@endnode

@node "Known Errors" "Known Errors"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}The following situations may cause error's:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}


  @{b}1. Global MIDI-Channel <> 0@{ub}

        Set <MIDI GLOBAL -> CH=1>


  @{b}2. False ModeID selected@{ub}

        Change Special/Instrument/..
        (03R/W-Users should do this first
         after launching KorgMAN .. sorry !)


  @{b}3. Bad/Cheap MIDI-Interface@{ub}

     There are known problems processing dumps
        with slow (cheap) MIDI-Interfaces !
            They simply loose bytes..


 @{b} 4. Using a X5 / X5DR@{ub}

        There are also known problems with these
           models, but I'm working on this ..
               .. so STAY TUNED :-))


  @{b}5. No MIDI/Instrument connected@{ub}

@{i}        ...@{ui}
@endnode

@node "The Past.." "The Past.."

 @{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}H i s t o r y@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}


   @{i}April '94@{ui} ..  buying this harmless looking though marvelous
                 sounding black box called Korg 05R/W



   @{i}April '95@{ui} ..  a bank full of nice sounds and no way saving
                 or dumping them in an acceptable way.

                 first trys receiving dumps via small programs



   @{i}May '95@{ui} ..    @{b}KorgMAN 1.0@{ub} (internal release)
                 quite buggy - but it work's !



   @{i}June '95@{ui} ..   @{b}KorgMAN 1.1@{ub}  -  first public release



   @{i}July@{ui} '96 ..  @{b} KorgMAN 1.5@{ub}  -  the story continues

                 @{u}New features@{uu}:   · 03R/W-Support  (thanks, Gary!)
                                 · sounds can be categorized
                                 · sort sounds by name and/or type
                                 · save bank as ASCII-file
                                 · added <Insert> - Action



  @{i} October '96@{ui} ..   @{b}KorgMAN 1.7@{ub}  -  some improvements

                    @{u}New features@{uu}:   · Preferences for SaveASCII
                                    · added <DoubleCheck> (function)
                                    · some general GUI-improvements
                                    · some smaller changes I'm
                                      too lazy to note down ..

                    @{u}Bugfixes@{uu}:   · 'NewLookMenu' didn't work right
                                · Doublecheck didn't always work correct
                                · bad path for loading/saving .. sorry !



  @{i}November '96@{ui}  ..  @{b}KorgMAN 1.7b@{ub}  -  bugfixes !

                    @{u}Bug's found/removed@{uu}:   · some bad Enforcer-Hit's
                                           · load bank/prog accepted
                                             bad files (NO prog/bank)..
                                           · 'Standard.Bk5' not found
                                             didn't quit KorgMAN
                                           · strange windowtitle ;-)




@{i}
 ..thanks again to the few people writing me letters/emails
   and encouraged me continue developing KorgMAN !@{ui}
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}F u t u r e@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}


   I've spent a lot of time developing KorgMAN.
   Although a few people wrote me letters they're
   happy finding such a program it's still a lot
   of work to keep on developing for a few people
   all over the world ..

   There'll definitely be some minor updates in
   the future but nothing big at all if there's
   no response.

   If@{b} you @{ub}want to encourage me continue developing
   KorgMAN send me a postcard from your hometown
   and tell me, how you'd like to have KorgMAN improved.
   If you would like me writing an editor, please note down,
   what you'd pay for it then.
   

     The future of KorgMAN depends on you ..



 @{b}Future plans@{ub}


   @{u}Features I'd like to add@{uu}:

        · implement <TestSound-Volume>

        · improve Type-Management

        · implement 'Combi'-Mode-Librarian
          including dynamic-program-managing

        · include 03R/W-Sounds

        · Convert 03 <-> 05 Sounds

        · add Prefs to customize User-Interface
          and options ..



@{i}        · IF there'll EVER be an editor, it may
          have some of this features:@{ui}

                      - State-of-the-art User-Interface
                        (Drag'n'Drop, great looking, ..)

                      - graphical Envelope-Editing

                      - Single-Program AND Combi-Editing

                      - integrated Program/Combi-Librarian
@endnode

